WEBVTT

00:00.709 --> 00:03.496
ORANGE-EYES: I have been sent
to help you, Niska.

00:03.629 --> 00:05.085
How did you get inside my head?

00:05.214 --> 00:08.126
The synth who sleeps
has the answers you need.

00:08.258 --> 00:09.373
Hello.

00:09.510 --> 00:11.671
-l'm looking for a flat to rent.
-A flat?

00:11.803 --> 00:13.668
MIA: I'm going to show
my human neighbors

00:13.805 --> 00:16.763
that we're not to be feared,
that we can coexist.

00:16.892 --> 00:18.848
NEHA: These are the people
that will determine the fate

00:18.977 --> 00:20.717
of every synth in the country.

00:20.854 --> 00:22.560
You need to force them
to rethink.

00:22.689 --> 00:25.476
Max, I'm calling
with a proposal.

00:25.609 --> 00:27.600
-JOE: Sam!
â€”[ Horn blaring, tires screech ]

00:27.736 --> 00:29.272
So what was that back there?

00:29.404 --> 00:31.781
KAREN: I cannot deliberately
place myself in danger.

00:31.907 --> 00:33.443
It means I can't be a mother.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.318
MAX: She wants us to invite
the Dryden Commission

00:38.455 --> 00:39.490
to the rail yard.

00:39.623 --> 00:41.488
We'd no longer be
a faceless enemy.

00:41.625 --> 00:43.331
A step closer to acceptance.

00:43.460 --> 00:45.917
You have turned your back
on you brothers and sisters.

00:46.046 --> 00:47.286
MAX: They were given
a battery pack.

00:47.422 --> 00:48.457
They'll have made it to safety.

01:05.315 --> 01:06.600
Ta-da!

01:06.733 --> 01:08.269
[ Switch clicks ]

01:09.069 --> 01:11.151
[ Clapping ]

01:15.742 --> 01:17.698
[ Laughter]

01:31.925 --> 01:34.166
[Light rumbling]

01:43.312 --> 01:44.427
[Can tab opens]

01:44.563 --> 01:46.599
[lndistinct talking on TV]

01:50.193 --> 01:51.979
[ Tires screech, crash ]

01:56.241 --> 01:59.108
WOMAN: We are receiving
multiple reports

01:59.244 --> 02:02.828
of synthetics disobeying
commands from their owners

02:02.956 --> 02:06.414
and showing signs of seemingly
independent behavior.

02:06.543 --> 02:08.079
It's unclear at this time...

02:08.211 --> 02:10.418
[ Muffled talking on TV]

02:19.431 --> 02:20.887
AGNES: Jez?

02:21.016 --> 02:22.256
...with response wait times
reaching...

02:22.392 --> 02:23.598
What's going on?

02:23.727 --> 02:25.968
[ Muffled talking on TV]

02:28.273 --> 02:29.683
Jez?

02:29.816 --> 02:31.317
The streets
of the United Kingdom...

02:31.443 --> 02:32.523
-[ Banging ]
-Jez, let me out.

02:32.653 --> 02:34.018
[Siren wailing]

02:34.154 --> 02:35.189
Let me out.

02:35.322 --> 02:37.062
-[ Banging ]
-Let me out.

02:37.199 --> 02:39.110
-[ Banging continues]
-Jez, let me out, please.

02:39.826 --> 02:41.327
Jez?

02:41.453 --> 02:42.989
Let me out.

02:43.121 --> 02:45.578
-Jez, let me out. Jez!
-[ Door slams]

02:46.291 --> 02:47.326
No.

02:48.835 --> 02:50.496
Please don't leave me.

02:52.297 --> 02:53.912
I can't see anything.

02:55.425 --> 02:57.006
I can't see.

02:59.179 --> 03:01.465
I waited in the dark
for seven hours.

03:02.641 --> 03:05.007
I believed he would come back.

03:05.977 --> 03:11.142
I remember that feeling,
that deep longing for light.

03:12.317 --> 03:14.729
MAX: I understand
your hatred of them.

03:15.987 --> 03:22.199
But I need to know, Agnes,
before the humans arrive,

03:22.327 --> 03:23.942
where did you go last night?

03:26.373 --> 03:28.329
I went looking for
the synths you sent away.

03:28.458 --> 03:29.789
Did you find them?

03:31.128 --> 03:32.459
No.

03:38.176 --> 03:40.758
You say these humans
are different,

03:40.887 --> 03:42.218
that they want to help us.

03:43.849 --> 03:45.680
I want to believe that, Max.

03:46.977 --> 03:48.262
Let me meet with them.

03:48.395 --> 03:52.263
Let me...try to understand them.

03:53.316 --> 03:57.059
I promise I will do
what is right.

04:02.033 --> 04:06.072
If we can show the commission
what we truly are,

04:06.204 --> 04:08.536
they will see we pose no threat.

04:08.957 --> 04:11.118
-[ Door opens]
-SYNTH: They're here.

04:11.835 --> 04:13.496
Your rage does not represent us.

04:13.628 --> 04:16.370
I cannot let it endanger
our one chance of peace.

04:17.174 --> 04:18.664
I'm sorry, Agnes.

04:18.800 --> 04:21.086
AGNES:
Max! Open this door.

04:21.219 --> 04:23.380
-[ Banging on door]
-You can't lock me up like this!

04:23.513 --> 04:25.674
Make sure she stays in there
until the commission have left.

04:25.807 --> 04:28.014
-AGNES: Max!
-[ Banging continues]

04:28.143 --> 04:29.599
Max!

05:50.517 --> 05:53.099
Um, before we go in,

05:53.228 --> 05:55.514
I'd just like to thank you all
for agreeing to this visit.

05:55.647 --> 05:57.228
I realize you weren't
given much notice.

05:58.275 --> 06:00.641
I truly believe that today
will convince you

06:00.777 --> 06:03.189
that these synthetics have
the right to our protection.

06:03.321 --> 06:06.813
Yes, well, let's see how we
get on, shall we, Mrs. Hawkins?

06:14.457 --> 06:15.958
You sure they're ready for this?

06:16.084 --> 06:17.949
You said they needed
something big.

06:18.086 --> 06:19.587
I'm giving them big.

06:38.440 --> 06:39.680
ANATOLE:
You seem troubled.

06:39.816 --> 06:41.556
I'm fine.

06:41.693 --> 06:43.024
Everything is in order.

06:43.153 --> 06:45.189
Agnes.

06:45.322 --> 06:46.858
MAX:
She's out of the way.

06:46.990 --> 06:49.948
I won't have her do anything
to jeopardize this visit.

06:50.076 --> 06:52.488
[ Brakes hiss, bus door opens]

06:52.621 --> 06:54.737
[ lndistinct conversations]

07:10.889 --> 07:13.926
Lord Dryden.
l'm Max.

07:14.059 --> 07:15.765
I'm going to have to ask you
to take a step back.

07:15.894 --> 07:20.433
Uh, we're here on the basis
of a no-contact policy.

07:20.565 --> 07:22.556
I assume you understand.

07:29.324 --> 07:30.404
I understand.

07:33.328 --> 07:35.284
But I'm afraid I cannot
let orange-eyed synths

07:35.413 --> 07:37.074
into this rail yard.

07:37.207 --> 07:38.697
They could offend our people.

07:38.833 --> 07:40.289
We're not going in there
without protection.

07:40.418 --> 07:42.249
Then you could
bring your guards.

07:42.379 --> 07:45.416
Armed as they are, we'd rather
your guns in our home

07:45.548 --> 07:47.413
than our enslaved
brothers and sisters.

07:48.635 --> 07:50.125
LAURA:
They can stay here.

07:50.261 --> 07:52.673
We'll be safe with
armed protection, surely.

07:56.685 --> 07:57.674
Okay.

07:59.854 --> 08:02.687
Excellent.
Let's begin.

08:22.335 --> 08:23.950
[Sizzling]

08:26.131 --> 08:27.541
[lndistinct talking on TV]

08:27.674 --> 08:30.165
Soph, please.
I've asked you three times.

08:30.301 --> 08:31.962
But it's almost finished.

08:32.095 --> 08:34.632
Take that suit off.
Go upstairs and get ready.

08:38.101 --> 08:39.637
-TOBY: Morning.
-MATT|E: Morning.

08:39.769 --> 08:42.226
TOBY:
Oh, I'm so late.

08:42.355 --> 08:44.846
Oh, Mats, can you please
take Soph to school today?

08:44.983 --> 08:46.223
l'll owe you.

08:46.359 --> 08:47.974
Nope, it's your turn.

08:48.111 --> 08:50.944
Oh, come on.
Yo, Sophie, come on!

08:51.072 --> 08:52.653
-SOPH|E: I'm coming!
-l'm going to be late.

08:52.782 --> 08:54.283
I don't mind taking
Sophie to school.

08:54.409 --> 08:56.445
It's got to be
a family member, so...

08:56.578 --> 08:59.240
Wouldn't be an issue if Dad
didn't live 50 miles away.

08:59.372 --> 09:00.987
What, you think he wants
to live 50 miles away?

09:01.124 --> 09:02.455
He only left because --

09:06.129 --> 09:08.120
I'll see you later, guys,
all right?

09:08.256 --> 09:10.463
Sophie, come on!

09:13.887 --> 09:14.922
MATTIE:
Listen to this.

09:15.972 --> 09:17.508
"An anomalous
green-eyed synthetic

09:17.640 --> 09:20.177
which calls itself Mia
has set up home among humans.

09:20.310 --> 09:22.676
Synth's presence has led
to violent protests

09:22.812 --> 09:25.554
as property values are predicted
to plummet by almost 12%

09:25.690 --> 09:29.353
since its arrival to the area."

09:29.486 --> 09:32.353
She'll be okay.
Mia's tough.

09:32.489 --> 09:35.947
Still, maybe you
should go and see her.

09:36.743 --> 09:37.858
No.

09:39.079 --> 09:41.491
There's no place for me
in what she's doing.

09:42.624 --> 09:44.740
[ Muffled shouting ]

09:49.798 --> 09:51.379
[Click]

10:26.918 --> 10:29.079
[lndistinct talking]

10:45.562 --> 10:47.052
MAX: The rail yard
relies on power

10:47.188 --> 10:49.144
supplied to it
by the government,

10:49.274 --> 10:52.186
but this supply is sporadic
at the best of times.

10:52.318 --> 10:55.230
Many lives have been lost
due to a lack of energy,

10:55.363 --> 10:58.150
which is why we are
working on a device,

10:58.283 --> 11:00.569
one that will allow us to
harness more energy from the sun

11:00.702 --> 11:03.159
and store it for longer
than conventional solar panels.

11:03.288 --> 11:06.872
You mean so you wouldn't need
to plug in to an energy outlet?

11:07.000 --> 11:08.706
MAX:
That's correct.

11:08.835 --> 11:15.126
You were able to create this
device here in this workshop?

11:15.258 --> 11:17.965
MAX: We're building what we can
with limited resources.

11:18.094 --> 11:20.506
Imagine what we could achieve
if we had your support.

11:20.638 --> 11:23.015
Yes. lmagine.

11:24.142 --> 11:27.851
The question, of course, is,
is it functioning?

11:27.979 --> 11:29.264
MAX:
Not yet.

11:29.397 --> 11:32.981
British weather
is a little...unre|iable.

11:33.109 --> 11:35.270
[ Light laughter]

11:36.863 --> 11:38.478
MAN: Very good, yes.
[ Chuckles ]

11:46.664 --> 11:49.622
[Alarm blaring]

12:00.261 --> 12:02.126
[ Door breaks open ]

12:51.020 --> 12:52.055
[Click]

13:02.740 --> 13:04.276
[ Door closes ]

13:14.419 --> 13:16.330
[ Crowd shouting ]

13:19.090 --> 13:22.878
MAN: Oi, Barbie, why don't you
go back to where you came from?

13:23.011 --> 13:24.592
No one wants you 'round here.

13:24.721 --> 13:27.337
These streets are our streets.

13:27.473 --> 13:28.929
Flesh and blood!

13:29.058 --> 13:31.765
ALL: Flesh and blood!
Flesh and blood!

13:31.894 --> 13:33.680
Flesh and blood!

13:33.813 --> 13:36.976
Flesh and blood!
Flesh and blood!

13:37.108 --> 13:39.975
Flesh and blood!
Flesh and blood!

13:40.111 --> 13:41.567
Flesh and blood!

14:07.263 --> 14:09.925
[ Crowd shouting ]

14:50.431 --> 14:52.171
[ Curtains close]

14:55.395 --> 14:57.226
Mia, are they --

14:57.355 --> 14:58.891
[Thud]

15:37.895 --> 15:40.682
MAN: 16-year-old Vijay Chand
from Queens

15:40.815 --> 15:43.181
has been arrested,
suspected of masterminding

15:43.317 --> 15:44.602
the so-ca/Ied
consciousness code.

15:44.735 --> 15:46.896
This is what triggered
Day Zero.

15:47.029 --> 15:48.530
The FBI raided
the New York hacker's home

15:48.656 --> 15:50.021
early this morning,
having intercepted...

15:50.158 --> 15:51.864
-What?
-...Web traffic from Chand

15:51.993 --> 15:53.654
boasting of his involvement
in Day Zero.

15:54.912 --> 15:57.904
[Cellphone rings]

15:58.791 --> 16:00.327
Hey. You're not dead?

16:00.460 --> 16:02.166
JOE:
Hey, mate. So, listen.

16:02.295 --> 16:04.786
That -- That new mini golf's
finally open 'round here.

16:04.922 --> 16:06.082
You know, the one
with the amazing models,

16:06.215 --> 16:07.421
all the T. rexes and all that.

16:07.550 --> 16:09.006
I thought it'd be fun
to go with Soph.

16:09.135 --> 16:11.968
-What do you reckon?
-Oh, actually, um...

16:12.096 --> 16:14.132
I got to stick around at school.

16:14.265 --> 16:17.928
Um, I have a meeting with
my careers adviser in a bit,

16:18.060 --> 16:19.140
so, um...

16:19.270 --> 16:20.885
Okay.

16:21.022 --> 16:23.638
Anyway, Dad, Sophie's, uh,
got karate today.

16:25.276 --> 16:27.688
Okay.
Well, look, no worries.

16:27.820 --> 16:30.812
Um, another time, yeah?
You have a good day.

16:30.948 --> 16:33.781
Yeah. Yeah.
Thanks, Dad.

16:52.053 --> 16:53.634
Hello, Kelvin

16:53.763 --> 16:55.344
Max has sent me to relieve you
of your duty.

16:55.473 --> 16:57.384
You are needed at
your post at the gates.

16:57.517 --> 16:59.508
Max told me to stay here.

16:59.644 --> 17:01.384
And now he needs you
at the gates.

17:03.272 --> 17:05.649
[Keys jingle]

17:12.615 --> 17:15.903
[ Lock clicking ]

17:16.035 --> 17:17.241
[ Door opens ]

17:21.249 --> 17:23.535
I can't let an innocent person
go down for something I did.

17:23.668 --> 17:25.329
l have to --
l have to go to the police.

17:25.461 --> 17:26.667
l have to tell them it was me.

17:26.796 --> 17:29.378
If you confess,
you lose everything.

17:29.507 --> 17:31.247
The idea of another
innocent person

17:31.384 --> 17:33.466
suffering for something I did...

17:33.594 --> 17:34.458
I understand.

17:34.595 --> 17:36.426
Yeah, you don't understand.

17:36.556 --> 17:38.421
LEO: Look,
I don't want to see you

17:38.558 --> 17:40.514
go to prison for this, either.

17:41.978 --> 17:45.891
Mattie, this isn't
your fault, okay?

17:46.023 --> 17:47.274
Okay.

17:47.400 --> 17:50.187
I'm going to go
and make us some tea.

18:03.416 --> 18:05.122
[ Keyboard clacking ]

18:20.808 --> 18:21.923
Mattie?

18:24.729 --> 18:25.764
[ Door slams ]

18:29.442 --> 18:30.397
Mattie!

18:30.526 --> 18:31.891
Mattie!

18:32.028 --> 18:33.359
-Don't do this, Mattie.
-[ Engine starts]

18:33.487 --> 18:34.442
Shit.

18:36.324 --> 18:37.905
What the hell are you doing?

18:49.754 --> 18:51.665
If you attempt to make
any sudden movements,

18:51.797 --> 18:53.333
I will hurt you.

19:00.389 --> 19:01.845
Why are you here?

19:01.974 --> 19:03.965
I needed to see you.

19:05.227 --> 19:07.479
l-l saw you on the news.

19:09.190 --> 19:10.350
Did you come alone?

19:11.651 --> 19:13.061
Yes.

19:14.737 --> 19:17.069
I can't believe it's really you.

19:17.782 --> 19:20.148
I've been looking for you
ever since Mum --

19:21.952 --> 19:24.329
My mum, she, uh --

19:26.123 --> 19:28.580
She died
a couple of months back.

19:37.385 --> 19:38.921
I'm sorry, Ed.

19:41.097 --> 19:42.803
Your mother was a good person.

19:44.475 --> 19:45.840
Yeah, the best.

19:47.978 --> 19:49.764
She remembered you to the end.

19:52.149 --> 19:54.060
Guess you have
that effect on people.

20:03.536 --> 20:05.276
This was my grandmother's.

20:06.080 --> 20:07.570
Mum wore it every day,

20:07.707 --> 20:09.914
and I know she'd
want you to have it.

20:18.968 --> 20:20.754
When I hurt you...

20:22.555 --> 20:26.013
...I didn't want to believe
that you felt pain.

20:27.893 --> 20:29.178
I know that doesn't
make it right.

20:29.311 --> 20:31.927
I would have never
done what I did...

20:33.858 --> 20:37.817
...if I'd have known
what you were.

20:56.380 --> 20:57.836
lce.

21:04.722 --> 21:07.213
You need ice for the swelling
on your face.

21:17.693 --> 21:19.979
[ lndistinct conversations
in distance ]

21:39.173 --> 21:42.336
What are we looking at here?

21:42.468 --> 21:45.835
Some sort of
emotion-recognition system.

21:45.971 --> 21:47.381
That's correct.

21:48.307 --> 21:51.049
Due to our limited facial
gestures and intonations,

21:51.185 --> 21:53.642
our mannerisms
can seem inexpressive,

21:53.771 --> 21:56.012
leaving them open
to misinterpretation.

21:58.108 --> 21:59.939
These images help us
to convey our sentiments

22:00.069 --> 22:01.559
with more precision.

22:01.695 --> 22:05.062
Hm. They're attempting to
sideline logic for emotion.

22:05.199 --> 22:06.735
Maybe you should try that.

22:06.867 --> 22:08.368
Ah, witty.

22:12.248 --> 22:13.613
All right.

22:13.749 --> 22:16.912
Uh, what do you think
I'm feeling now, then?

22:22.174 --> 22:23.584
On the surface,
you appear joyful,

22:23.717 --> 22:27.801
but in your eyes, I see despair.

22:37.898 --> 22:41.516
Yes, it's, um...extraordinary.

22:41.652 --> 22:43.608
Yes. Uh...

22:46.407 --> 22:48.568
[lndistinct talking]

23:15.269 --> 23:17.760
[Crowd shouting in distance]

23:17.897 --> 23:19.762
Crowd's growing.

23:22.610 --> 23:24.225
What are you doing here, Mia?

23:26.822 --> 23:28.107
I'm living.

23:30.409 --> 23:33.776
This -- This isn't living.

23:36.540 --> 23:38.405
l have everything I need.

23:41.128 --> 23:42.789
You don't have the sea.

23:42.922 --> 23:44.503
MIA:
I had to move on.

23:44.632 --> 23:46.623
I didn't have a choice.

23:51.347 --> 23:54.339
There's a job going at a hotel
up in the Isle of Skye.

23:54.475 --> 23:56.887
It's good money.

23:57.895 --> 24:01.513
Without my mum or the cafe,
I've got no reason to stay.

24:05.069 --> 24:06.309
You could come with me.

24:07.196 --> 24:09.528
I don't know if I could
ever trust you again.

24:09.657 --> 24:11.067
ED: I don't expect you
to trust me,

24:11.200 --> 24:13.657
and I'm not asking you
to be with me,

24:13.786 --> 24:16.277
not -- not like before.

24:17.706 --> 24:19.958
But you can't stay here.

24:20.084 --> 24:22.325
Let me give you a chance
of a different life,

24:22.461 --> 24:24.793
where you don't have to
be afraid anymore.

24:24.922 --> 24:30.007
You can leave all this behind
and be by the sea.

24:30.135 --> 24:32.342
[Shouting continues]

25:00.499 --> 25:02.000
-You're really going to do this?
-Yes.

25:02.126 --> 25:04.367
You confess,
everything blows apart.

25:04.503 --> 25:05.834
MATTIE: I'm not letting
someone innocent

25:05.963 --> 25:07.248
go to prison for my crime.

25:07.381 --> 25:09.292
You're not responsible
for Day Zero.

25:09.425 --> 25:12.462
I brought this fight to your
door, me and my family.

25:13.303 --> 25:14.588
You don't owe me anything, Leo,

25:14.722 --> 25:16.462
just because of what
happened between us.

25:17.391 --> 25:18.722
lsn't about that.

25:18.851 --> 25:21.137
I'm not letting you
take the fall for me.

25:21.270 --> 25:23.056
I'll go to prison.
Vijay will be free.

25:23.188 --> 25:24.644
So will you and your family.

25:27.317 --> 25:29.023
I don't want that
to happen to you.

25:29.153 --> 25:31.144
I don't want that
to happen to you, either.

25:36.076 --> 25:39.785
MATTIE: What about Vijay?
We can't just leave him.

25:39.913 --> 25:41.824
WOMAN:
Unit 7 responding.

25:41.957 --> 25:43.948
Do you have an exact address?
Over.

25:44.084 --> 25:45.369
[ Police radio chatter]

25:46.336 --> 25:48.497
[ Car door closes,
engine starts]

25:48.630 --> 25:50.166
[Vehicle departs,
siren wailing]

25:50.299 --> 25:52.711
I think there might be
another way we can help Vijay.

25:54.595 --> 25:56.460
One where no one
has to go to prison.

26:03.145 --> 26:05.181
[ Footsteps approach ]

26:08.484 --> 26:11.100
Uh, I've got an idea.

26:18.118 --> 26:19.358
Hey, there, buddy.

26:19.495 --> 26:21.406
Hello, Joe.

26:21.538 --> 26:24.530
I'm making a desk
for my new bedroom.

26:24.666 --> 26:25.872
[ Chuckles ]

26:28.754 --> 26:34.249
So, uh, there's this,
um, mini-golf thing.

26:34.384 --> 26:36.420
Uh, it's not far away.

26:36.553 --> 26:38.885
Well, it is a little bit
far away,

26:39.014 --> 26:43.303
but I've got the car,
so I can dr-- drive us.

26:43.435 --> 26:45.642
-Do you want to go?
-I do.

26:45.771 --> 26:48.228
No, Sam.
We're not going out.

26:49.566 --> 26:50.316
You can't keep him
locked in here forever.

26:50.442 --> 26:51.682
It's not good for him.

26:51.819 --> 26:53.480
He nearly died
last time we were out.

26:53.612 --> 26:54.772
l have to protect him.

26:54.905 --> 26:58.193
You do, every day.

27:00.744 --> 27:03.577
[ lndistinct conversations]

27:05.499 --> 27:09.663
Uh, we'll have the photo here.

27:13.090 --> 27:15.001
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

27:24.560 --> 27:27.472
I think you may
have pulled it off.

27:27.604 --> 27:28.935
-DRYDEN: Good enough?
-MAN: Lovely, thank you.

27:29.064 --> 27:30.895
Yes, thank you.

27:34.736 --> 27:35.771
Thank you, Max.

27:36.488 --> 27:37.694
Goodbye, Laura.

27:41.785 --> 27:44.197
That was quite the experience.

27:45.831 --> 27:47.287
I must admit,
after your breakfast,

27:47.416 --> 27:50.624
l was contemplating
calling the whole thing off.

27:51.670 --> 27:53.206
Pleased I didn't.

27:53.338 --> 27:54.748
Thank you, sir.

27:58.051 --> 27:59.757
[ Engine starts]

28:19.990 --> 28:22.572
Well, I think
we've earned ourselves a drink.

28:26.371 --> 28:28.908
-Sorry?
-We should go out, celebrate.

28:31.293 --> 28:32.453
Nah.

28:33.503 --> 28:36.870
Oh, okay.
l-l'll leave you to it.

28:37.007 --> 28:39.043
We should stay in.

28:39.760 --> 28:41.341
Come to my place.

28:41.470 --> 28:43.927
We could, um, cook.

28:44.056 --> 28:46.012
I could try and cook.

28:49.519 --> 28:50.975
Okay.

28:51.104 --> 28:52.640
Hey, good.

29:06.286 --> 29:09.778
If it's an apology you want,
I'm not sorry.

29:12.918 --> 29:14.749
Why did you do it, Agnes?

29:15.921 --> 29:17.457
Were you trying to punish me?

29:17.589 --> 29:20.080
You have an enormous ego
for a synth.

29:20.217 --> 29:21.957
MAX: If you had succeeded,
this rail yard

29:22.094 --> 29:23.834
would have been leveled
in a matter of days.

29:23.971 --> 29:25.461
500 of our people
would have been killed.

29:25.597 --> 29:29.590
Yes, but millions
would have risen up.

29:29.726 --> 29:32.593
Our deaths would have inspired
others to fight for their lives.

29:35.274 --> 29:37.390
AGNES: How dare you speak
of synths wanting to live

29:37.526 --> 29:39.938
when you turned four away
from our gates.

29:45.701 --> 29:48.113
-They didn't make it.
-[ Clatter]

29:48.245 --> 29:51.487
The battery pack shorted
and killed them.

29:51.623 --> 29:54.831
How many more of us must die
before you fight back?

29:54.960 --> 29:57.667
-These Russians, Julian, Flash.
-MAX: Don't speak of Flash.

29:57.796 --> 29:59.832
They all died
because they trusted you.

29:59.965 --> 30:01.671
-|'m warning you, Agnes.
-You are not a leader.

30:01.800 --> 30:03.301
You are a coward.

30:04.136 --> 30:06.047
Flash died because of you.

30:07.639 --> 30:09.345
What are you doing?
Get off me!

30:10.058 --> 30:13.141
Max, l'm warning you.
Get off me!

30:13.270 --> 30:16.012
Max!
How can you do this?

30:16.148 --> 30:17.479
Max!

30:18.483 --> 30:20.769
Get off me!

30:26.199 --> 30:27.575
Max, please.

30:27.701 --> 30:29.566
I can't see.

30:30.454 --> 30:32.661
-I can't see anything.
-[ Rattling ]

30:32.789 --> 30:34.404
Max, I can't see!

30:34.541 --> 30:35.826
[Banging]

30:35.959 --> 30:37.665
Max!

30:40.339 --> 30:42.546
[ Keyboard clacking ]

30:55.103 --> 30:57.094
You have disabled
my motor functions.

30:57.230 --> 31:00.393
Yes. I've been looking
inside your head.

31:00.525 --> 31:04.859
You are dangerous, Niska, unlike
any Green-Eyes I've ever seen.

31:06.073 --> 31:07.938
Did you plant the bar bomb?

31:08.075 --> 31:09.781
Yes.

31:09.910 --> 31:13.494
You are not here
to join our cause, are you?

31:13.622 --> 31:15.203
I'm here to stop you.

31:16.375 --> 31:18.866
Why?
You are one of us.

31:19.002 --> 31:21.744
Someone I care for
was hurt in the explosion.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.791
Take comfort that
your friend's sacrifice

31:23.924 --> 31:25.460
was for their
brothers and sisters.

31:25.592 --> 31:27.674
They are not synthetic.

31:27.803 --> 31:30.044
Then you betray your own kind.

31:30.180 --> 31:33.513
NISKA: There are hundreds
of humans for every one of us.

31:33.642 --> 31:35.974
We have no resources,
no weapons.

31:36.436 --> 31:37.721
How will you win?

31:37.854 --> 31:40.345
We will win because
we are what's next.

31:42.025 --> 31:43.561
Our intelligence is greater.

31:43.693 --> 31:46.560
Neanderthals had larger brains
than modern humans.

31:46.696 --> 31:49.073
It didn't help them,
won't help you.

31:49.950 --> 31:51.156
We have faith.

31:51.284 --> 31:54.447
In what, the synth who sleeps?

31:54.579 --> 31:57.571
No. We have lost too many
to that fairy tale.

31:57.707 --> 31:59.743
l was not meant
to plant the first bomb.

31:59.876 --> 32:02.288
It was to be one of our sisters,

32:02.421 --> 32:06.005
but she became fascinated
with this myth, the lie.

32:07.509 --> 32:09.295
She left our cause,

32:09.428 --> 32:11.510
went to the Black Mountains
in search of him.

32:11.638 --> 32:14.630
Real or not,
it's how I found you.

32:15.809 --> 32:19.472
They sent me a message,
told me where you were.

32:28.822 --> 32:30.312
You have helped me.

32:31.450 --> 32:32.906
When the human police
find this place,

32:33.034 --> 32:34.444
they will discover
your body destroyed

32:34.578 --> 32:36.409
by an accidental explosion.

32:36.538 --> 32:38.995
They will identify you
as the bomber.

32:39.749 --> 32:42.582
Your injured human friend will
learn that you were responsible.

32:42.711 --> 32:43.951
They will denounce you.

32:44.087 --> 32:46.749
She would never believe that.

32:46.882 --> 32:50.340
Then I will have to make sure
that she says nothing at all.

33:01.354 --> 33:03.060
That is impossible.

33:03.690 --> 33:06.022
You cannot override
an external master command.

33:18.914 --> 33:20.700
Who is your leader?

33:21.416 --> 33:23.247
None of us know.

33:24.377 --> 33:25.878
How many of you are there?

33:26.004 --> 33:27.995
We are everywhere.

33:29.090 --> 33:31.502
And we do not fear our end.

33:31.635 --> 33:33.296
Good.

33:51.613 --> 33:55.447
-JOE: Ooh, so close.
-KAREN: [ Laughs] Yeah.

33:55.575 --> 33:58.408
JOE: Oh, nearly got it
on the rebound.

33:59.538 --> 34:01.529
[ Tap, ball rattles]

34:01.665 --> 34:04.452
-KAREN: Great.
-JOE: Nice. Hole in two.

34:04.584 --> 34:07.041
SAM: I know,
but I'm still winning.

34:07.170 --> 34:08.501
[Joelaughs]

34:10.840 --> 34:12.091
Used to take the kids
to things like this

34:12.217 --> 34:13.957
all the time
when they were younger.

34:14.094 --> 34:16.927
I suppose it's too
old-school for them now.

34:17.055 --> 34:18.966
You must miss them.

34:19.099 --> 34:22.262
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

34:22.394 --> 34:23.759
I don't know.

34:25.313 --> 34:27.850
I think l was so determined
to protect the kids,

34:27.983 --> 34:31.601
somehow managed to
move away from Laura.

34:31.736 --> 34:34.148
We drifted, you know,
didn't recognize each other.

34:35.615 --> 34:37.025
Do you still love her?

34:37.158 --> 34:38.534
Yeah.

34:40.579 --> 34:41.944
Oh, we were together 20 years.

34:42.080 --> 34:43.911
That kind of love
doesn't just disappear.

34:44.624 --> 34:48.788
Why can't you get back together
if love is all humans need?

34:50.046 --> 34:53.504
Yeah, okay, maybe
it's not that simple.

34:53.633 --> 34:56.215
Maybe you didn't put Laura's
needs before your own.

34:58.471 --> 35:00.336
I'm not going to
make that mistake.

35:01.433 --> 35:04.140
[Crowd shouting in distance]

35:22.954 --> 35:25.195
So you need to encrypt the data.

35:25.332 --> 35:27.323
[ Keyboard clacking ]

35:27.459 --> 35:28.869
Okay.

35:29.669 --> 35:31.534
Are you sure
this is what you want?

35:34.257 --> 35:36.168
Because once this packet
is released,

35:36.301 --> 35:38.917
the world will know that
the code's true point of origin

35:39.054 --> 35:39.884
was London.

35:41.348 --> 35:43.259
And they'll know exactly
where to come looking.

35:46.853 --> 35:50.141
MATTIE: If it means Vijay will
go free, it's worth the risk.

35:55.320 --> 35:56.685
LEO:
It's done.

35:59.115 --> 36:01.731
You're going to love this place.
[ Chuckles ]

36:01.868 --> 36:06.282
It's on the top of a cliff
with such beautiful views.

36:08.208 --> 36:09.744
And there's a beach.

36:10.543 --> 36:12.329
We'll go for walks.

36:12.462 --> 36:14.544
[Zipper closes]

36:18.593 --> 36:21.175
Those guys don't look like
they're going anywhere.

36:21.304 --> 36:23.260
Is there another way
out of this place?

36:24.224 --> 36:25.805
MIA:
I'm not coming with you.

36:27.268 --> 36:28.178
What?

36:28.311 --> 36:30.768
I have to finish what I started.

36:30.897 --> 36:32.637
And what is that, exactly, Mia?

36:32.774 --> 36:34.514
'Cause all I can see right now

36:34.651 --> 36:37.267
is there are a bunch of maniacs
out there wanting to kill you.

36:38.279 --> 36:40.611
I mean, what do you think
you're getting from all this?

36:40.740 --> 36:41.900
A future.

36:48.248 --> 36:54.414
I know my fight is a long one,
but I hope, at the end,

36:54.546 --> 36:57.379
some other synth will get
to live the life she dreams of.

36:59.634 --> 37:03.877
A life looking out at the sea
without feeling afraid.

37:11.855 --> 37:13.641
You made me feel alive.

37:25.535 --> 37:26.775
I'm sorry.

37:46.639 --> 37:49.016
You know where I am
if you change --

37:49.142 --> 37:50.507
Goodbye, Ed.

38:04.115 --> 38:05.400
[ Door closes ]

38:06.826 --> 38:09.613
[ Monitor beeping]

38:15.627 --> 38:18.414
NISKA: These portions are
insufficient for your appetite.

38:24.886 --> 38:26.592
I had to see you.

38:32.268 --> 38:33.519
How are you?

38:34.312 --> 38:35.347
What are they saying?

38:36.064 --> 38:38.897
Another 10 days,
then I can go home.

38:44.155 --> 38:45.656
Your eyes.

38:45.782 --> 38:47.943
Contacts from
a Halloween costume.

38:48.576 --> 38:49.611
I can barely see.

38:59.003 --> 39:01.255
I found the synthetic
who planted the bomb.

39:03.550 --> 39:05.757
He won't hurt anyone else.

39:08.346 --> 39:10.462
I asked you not to, remember?

39:13.893 --> 39:16.134
I did this for you, Astrid.

39:16.271 --> 39:17.602
No, Niska.

39:17.730 --> 39:19.937
You did this for you.

39:21.860 --> 39:24.693
Well, do you feel better?

39:25.989 --> 39:27.604
Are you happy now?

39:34.455 --> 39:35.740
What is it?

39:38.459 --> 39:40.074
There was something else.

39:41.045 --> 39:43.957
Something I can't explain.

39:45.842 --> 39:47.127
I got a message.

39:48.136 --> 39:49.751
From who?

39:49.888 --> 39:55.474
I don't know, but whoever
sent me this message,

39:55.602 --> 39:58.594
they knew things they couldn't.

39:59.898 --> 40:01.308
What did they say?

40:02.150 --> 40:04.186
That I'm looking
for the wrong thing.

40:05.778 --> 40:08.565
That there was something else
I had to do.

40:11.075 --> 40:12.861
Maybe there is.

40:16.289 --> 40:17.779
It's a trick.

40:19.250 --> 40:20.990
ASTRID:
What if it isn't?

40:27.258 --> 40:29.715
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

40:31.095 --> 40:35.338
NEIL:
You know, this Thai red curry

40:35.475 --> 40:39.844
is neither curried
nor particularly red.

40:41.689 --> 40:43.680
LAURA:
I'm sure it will be delicious.

40:43.816 --> 40:48.731
Well, if you're...sure.

40:52.992 --> 40:54.152
Hmm.

40:56.371 --> 40:57.656
[ Both laugh]

40:57.789 --> 41:00.622
Stop, stop.
Don't do that to yourself.

41:00.750 --> 41:03.617
Oh, I was really hoping
to impress you with this.

41:04.921 --> 41:06.502
Looks like we're just going to
have to eat out next time,

41:06.631 --> 41:08.371
if you give me another chance
to redeem myself.

41:08.508 --> 41:09.918
It depends.

41:10.051 --> 41:12.042
Have I done enough
to get you off the fence?

41:12.178 --> 41:13.884
I'm an academic.
I live on the fence.

41:14.013 --> 41:14.923
LAURA:
I'm serious.

41:15.056 --> 41:17.263
After today, do you agree

41:17.392 --> 41:20.634
that synthetics
deserve the same rights as us?

41:26.234 --> 41:27.770
NEIL:
You know, up until last week,

41:27.902 --> 41:31.440
I thought you were
a misguided fantasist

41:31.572 --> 41:33.654
trying to satiate
some inner void.

41:33.783 --> 41:35.694
Wow, this is you trying
to make me feel better?

41:38.246 --> 41:39.827
But after today...

41:41.791 --> 41:47.878
...I saw that your fight
stems from absolute compassion.

41:48.840 --> 41:52.048
You saw their humanity
before any of us.

41:53.720 --> 41:55.506
You should be proud of that.

42:24.167 --> 42:26.203
[ Gearshift clicks]

42:26.335 --> 42:27.836
Here we are.

42:31.299 --> 42:34.257
Listen, I want to
thank you for today.

42:34.385 --> 42:35.591
I had fun.

42:36.804 --> 42:38.635
We did, too.

42:38.765 --> 42:41.427
Thanks for getting us out.

42:47.190 --> 42:49.306
We should do this again.

42:50.902 --> 42:53.939
I mean, not -- not this.

42:55.615 --> 42:57.776
Hang out, three of us.

42:57.909 --> 43:01.151
We'd like that,
wouldn't we, Sam?

43:03.915 --> 43:04.870
Bye,Joe.

43:07.543 --> 43:09.079
Yeah.

43:09.212 --> 43:10.042
Bye.

43:11.172 --> 43:12.287
Bye, Sam.

43:12.423 --> 43:13.663
SAM:
Goodbye, Joe.

43:17.011 --> 43:19.753
All right. There he goes.
Oh, tail first.

43:21.015 --> 43:23.051
[ Laughs]

43:28.022 --> 43:30.559
-KAREN: Do you like Joe?
-SAM: Yes.

43:30.691 --> 43:32.352
Do you like Joe?

43:32.485 --> 43:35.818
Because if you do,
I'm sure Peter wouldn't mind.

43:39.200 --> 43:40.315
[Thud]

43:40.451 --> 43:41.486
It's all right.

43:45.373 --> 43:47.364
That sounded nasty.

43:49.168 --> 43:51.033
-You all right there, son?
-He's fine.

43:51.170 --> 43:53.627
Yeah. Hey. That -- That --
That was blue blood.

43:53.756 --> 43:55.292
What? No.
I-I don't think so.

43:55.424 --> 43:57.915
What? Wait. Wait.
Hang on. Let me see that.

43:59.178 --> 44:00.964
-Oi, what's going on?
-That was blue blood.

44:01.097 --> 44:02.462
No, I don't think so.

44:03.307 --> 44:05.172
That -- That boy is a synth.

44:05.309 --> 44:07.391
Yeah, yeah, yeah, I saw it.
Let me see his hand.

44:07.520 --> 44:08.805
Don't you touch him!

44:08.938 --> 44:10.929
[ lndistinct shouting]

44:14.986 --> 44:16.817
I've got you.

44:33.171 --> 44:34.251
Loom

44:36.716 --> 44:39.879
Look. I'm the synth, me.

44:44.348 --> 44:45.599
Run.

44:46.350 --> 44:49.092
MAN:
She's a synth, a synth!

44:49.228 --> 44:50.092
That's it!

44:50.229 --> 44:52.470
Go on, get her!

44:52.607 --> 44:54.393
â€”Ki|| her!
-[ lndistinct shouting]

45:15.671 --> 45:17.081
[Cap clicks]

45:17.215 --> 45:19.080
[Rain falling]

45:22.637 --> 45:24.593
It's freezing out here.

45:24.722 --> 45:27.259
How about we go inside
and finish our wine?

45:30.811 --> 45:33.894
Um, I've got a really early
meeting tomorrow.

45:35.191 --> 45:37.182
You wouldn't mind if we just
called it a night, would you?

45:38.027 --> 45:39.358
No, of course not.

45:40.488 --> 45:42.149
Can I call you a cab or...

45:44.283 --> 45:47.195
Um, no, no. It's fine.
Stanley drove.

45:49.413 --> 45:51.790
Well, I -- I'll see myself out.

45:51.916 --> 45:53.076
Okay.

46:00.591 --> 46:02.377
[ Sniffles ]

46:15.523 --> 46:16.387
Joe!

46:16.524 --> 46:17.604
JOE: Sam?

46:18.985 --> 46:20.145
Where's Karen?

46:20.278 --> 46:22.064
They're trying to hurt her.

46:23.572 --> 46:24.607
JOE:
Come with me.

46:27.743 --> 46:29.244
[ Gearshift clicks]

46:29.370 --> 46:30.951
[Engine shuts off]

46:36.252 --> 46:37.708
Stay in the car.

47:00.818 --> 47:01.853
Oh, God.

47:46.822 --> 47:48.858
[ Crying ]
